{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"0ff853e8-e3ac-4604-ae41-6e1d7de9795b","content":"Yes, you'll hit compatibility issues. Here's the breakdown:\n\n**Framework support dropped in MSTest v3:**\n- ❌ **`netcoreapp3.1`** — not supported (EOL)\n- ❌ **`net5.0`** — not supported (EOL)\n- ✅ **`net462`** — still supported\n\nYou'd need to retarget `netcoreapp3.1` and `net5.0` to a supported framework like `net6.0` or `net8.0`.\n\n**Package changes:** MSTest v3 consolidates `MSTest.TestFramework` + `MSTest.TestAdapter` into a single **`MSTest`** package, so you can simplify your `<ItemGroup>`.\n\n**Other notable breaking changes** in v3 include stricter test lifecycle behavior, some removed/renamed APIs, and changes to default timeout handling. Review the [MSTest v3 migration guide](https://learn.microsoft.com/dotnet/core/testing/mstest-sdk-overview) before upgrading.\n\nWould you like me to update the `.csproj` to be MSTest v3–compatible?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"17a2209e-1e15-4337-9df1-0469b29b8a1a","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user's project targets `net5.0`, `net462`, and `netcoreapp3.1`. They want to migrate from MSTest v2 (2.2.10) to MSTest v3.\n\nMSTest v3 has some important compatibility changes:\n\n1. **Dropped framework support**: MSTest v3 drops support for older target frameworks. Specifically:\n   - `.NET 5.0` is no longer supported (it's end-of-life)\n   - `.NET Core 3.1` is no longer supported (it's end-of-life)\n   - `.NET Framework 4.6.2` — I need to check this. MSTest v3 supports .NET Framework 4.6.2 and later, so `net462` should still be supported.\n   \nActually, let me clarify the exact support matrix. MSTest v3 only supports .NET Framework 4.6.2 and later, plus .NET 6.0 and newer LTS versions. That means `netcoreapp3.1` and `net5.0` won't work with MSTest v3 — the user would need to update those target frameworks. On the bright side, MSTest v3 consolidates the package ecosystem, so instead of managing separate `MSTest.TestFramework` and `MSTest.TestAdapter` packages, they can use the single `MSTest` meta-package.","outputTokens":791,"requestId":"A029:3A9E72:FD45B7:12C06C9:69FEA064"},"id":"092aea63-6e19-4fe8-a3d4-aab918923807","timestamp":"2026-05-09T02:48:19.410Z","parentId":"a79f0262-e136-4aa8-aa5b-40510d4ddd78"}
